description:
This dashboard shows the metrics, traces and logs ingested.  Please follow the following guides to control your data sent to SigNoz. Only last 15 minutes of data is shown as this is mainly intended to help you understand the recent volume. 

Metrics: https://signoz.io/docs/userguide/drop-metrics/


Logs: https://signoz.io/docs/logs-management/guides/drop-logs/


Traces: https://signoz.io/docs/traces-management/guides/drop-spans/
title: IngestionV2

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT count() FROM signoz_metrics.distributed_samples_v4 WHERE (metric_name NOT LIKE 'signoz_%') AND (metric_name NOT LIKE 'chi_%') AND unix_milli >= toUnixTimestamp(now() - INTERVAL 15 MINUTE) * 1000

widgets.description: This table contain the metric name and it's total samples count. Note: name of the metric is normalized.

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT count() AS Count, metric_name AS "Normalized Metric Name" FROM signoz_metrics.distributed_samples_v4 WHERE (metric_name NOT LIKE 'signoz_%') AND (metric_name NOT LIKE 'chi_%') AND unix_milli >= toUnixTimestamp(now() - INTERVAL 15 MINUTE) * 1000 GROUP BY metric_name ORDER BY Count DESC LIMIT 100

widgets.title: Volume breakdown by metric name

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT metric_name AS "Normalized Metric Name", `deployment.environment` AS "Deployment Environment", count() AS "Count" FROM signoz_metrics.distributed_samples_v4 INNER JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT fingerprint, JSONExtractString(labels, 'deployment.environment') AS `deployment.environment` FROM signoz_metrics.time_series_v4_1day WHERE (metric_name NOT LIKE 'signoz_%') AND (metric_name NOT LIKE 'chi_%') AND (unix_milli >= intDiv($start_timestamp_ms, 86400000) * 86400000) AND (unix_milli < $end_timestamp_ms)) AS filtered_time_series USING fingerprint WHERE unix_milli >= toUnixTimestamp(now() - INTERVAL 15 MINUTE) * 1000 GROUP BY metric_name, `deployment.environment` ORDER BY count() DESC LIMIT 100

widgets.title: Volume breakdown by deployment environment and metric name

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT `deployment.environment` AS "Deployment Environment", count() AS "Count" FROM signoz_metrics.distributed_samples_v4 INNER JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT fingerprint, JSONExtractString(labels, 'deployment.environment') AS `deployment.environment` FROM signoz_metrics.time_series_v4_1day WHERE (metric_name NOT LIKE 'signoz_%') AND (metric_name NOT LIKE 'chi_%') AND (unix_milli >= intDiv($start_timestamp_ms, 86400000) * 86400000) AND (unix_milli < $end_timestamp_ms)) AS filtered_time_series USING fingerprint WHERE unix_milli >= toUnixTimestamp(now() - INTERVAL 15 MINUTE) * 1000 GROUP BY `deployment.environment` ORDER BY count() DESC LIMIT 100

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT metric_name AS "Normalized Metric Name", `service.name` AS "Service Name", count() AS "Count" FROM signoz_metrics.distributed_samples_v4 INNER JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT fingerprint, JSONExtractString(labels, 'service.name') AS `service.name` FROM signoz_metrics.time_series_v4_1day WHERE (metric_name NOT LIKE 'signoz_%') AND (metric_name NOT LIKE 'chi_%') AND (unix_milli >= intDiv($start_timestamp_ms, 86400000) * 86400000) AND (unix_milli < $end_timestamp_ms)) AS filtered_time_series USING fingerprint WHERE unix_milli >= toUnixTimestamp(now() - INTERVAL 15 MINUTE) * 1000 GROUP BY metric_name, `service.name` ORDER BY count() DESC LIMIT 100

widgets.title: Metrics ingestion; Tables show only top 100 by volume

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT metric_name AS "Normalized Metric Name", `host.name` AS "Host Name", if(count() > 0, 'Yes', 'No') AS "Has Data" FROM signoz_metrics.distributed_samples_v4 INNER JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT fingerprint, JSONExtractString(labels, 'host.name') AS `host.name` FROM signoz_metrics.time_series_v4_1day WHERE (metric_name NOT LIKE 'signoz_%') AND (metric_name NOT LIKE 'chi_%') AND (unix_milli >= intDiv($start_timestamp_ms, 86400000) * 86400000) AND (unix_milli < $end_timestamp_ms)) AS filtered_time_series USING fingerprint WHERE unix_milli >= toUnixTimestamp(now() - INTERVAL 15 MINUTE) * 1000 GROUP BY metric_name, `host.name` ORDER BY `host.name` DESC

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT metric_name AS "Normalized Metric Name", `k8s.cluster.name` AS "K8s Cluster Name", `k8s.node.name` AS "K8s Node Name", `k8s.namespace.name` AS "K8s Namespace Name", if(count() > 0, 'Yes', 'No') AS "Has Data" FROM signoz_metrics.distributed_samples_v4 INNER JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT fingerprint, JSONExtractString(labels, 'k8s.cluster.name') AS `k8s.cluster.name`, JSONExtractString(labels, 'k8s.node.name') AS `k8s.node.name`, JSONExtractString(labels, 'k8s.namespace.name') AS `k8s.namespace.name` FROM signoz_metrics.time_series_v4_1day WHERE (metric_name NOT LIKE 'signoz_%') AND (metric_name NOT LIKE 'chi_%') AND (unix_milli >= intDiv($start_timestamp_ms, 86400000) * 86400000) AND (unix_milli < $end_timestamp_ms)) AS filtered_time_series USING fingerprint WHERE unix_milli >= toUnixTimestamp(now() - INTERVAL 15 MINUTE) * 1000 GROUP BY metric_name, `k8s.cluster.name`, `k8s.node.name`, `k8s.namespace.name` ORDER BY metric_name DESC, `k8s.cluster.name` DESC, `k8s.node.name` DESC, `k8s.namespace.name` DESC

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT `env` AS "Deployment Environment", metric_name AS "Noramalized Metric Name", `service.name` AS "Service Name", if(ceiling(divide(min(diff), 1000)) > 86400000, -1, ceiling(divide(min(diff), 1000))) AS max_diff_in_secs FROM (SELECT `env`, metric_name, `service.name`, unix_milli - lagInFrame(unix_milli, 1, 0) OVER rate_window AS diff FROM signoz_metrics.distributed_samples_v4 INNER JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT `env`, metric_name, JSONExtractString(labels, 'service.name') AS `service.name`, anyLast(fingerprint) AS fingerprint FROM signoz_metrics.time_series_v4_1day WHERE metric_name NOT LIKE 'signoz_%' AND (unix_milli >= intDiv($start_timestamp_ms, 86400000) * 86400000) AND (unix_milli < $end_timestamp_ms) GROUP BY `env`, metric_name, `service.name`) AS filtered_time_series USING fingerprint WHERE unix_milli >= (toUnixTimestamp(now() - toIntervalMinute(30)) * 1000) WINDOW rate_window as ( PARTITION BY fingerprint ORDER BY fingerprint, unix_milli)) WHERE diff > 0 GROUP BY `env`, metric_name, `service.name` ORDER BY `env`, metric_name, `service.name`

widgets.title: The observed report interval for (metric, service) combination

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT tagKey AS "Attribute Name", if(tagType = 'tag', 'Span Attribute', 'Span Resource Attribute') AS "Type" FROM signoz_traces.distributed_span_attributes_keys WHERE isColumn = false GROUP BY tagKey, tagType

widgets.title: Logs count by log file path

clickhouse_sql.name: A
clickhouse_sql.query: SELECT DISTINCT name, 'Log Record Attribute' AS Type FROM signoz_logs.distributed_logs_attribute_keys UNION ALL SELECT DISTINCT name, 'Log Resource Attribute' AS Type FROM signoz_logs.distributed_logs_resource_keys
